&lt;/ref&gt;
when these five naked-eye planets were visible in the vicinity of the Sun in the sky.

===1987===
[[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]], [[Venus]] and [[Mars]] separately reached conjunction with each other, and each separately with the Sun, within a 7-day period in August 1987 as seen from the Earth. The Moon also reached conjunction with each of these bodies on 24 August. However, none of these conjunctions were observable due to the glare of the Sun.&lt;ref name=&quot;meeus_astrontables1983&quot; /&gt;
